data.description: Stunning Townhome in Desirable Boone High School District! Experience the allure of this beautifully updated townhome nestled just 2 miles east of Orlando Health Arnold Palmer Hospital and moments from vibrant downtown Orlando. Revel in the ambiance of a single-family residence without the constraints of an HOA. From the moment you step onto the welcoming covered front porch, the value is evident: Andersen front door, inground sprinklers, a spacious one-car garage plus driveway parking, and a fully fenced backyard haven, poised for your custom touches – perhaps a stone courtyard or pool, under the canopy of mature trees. Inside, a grand entrance ushers you to a half bathroom, state-of-the-art chef’s kitchen – gleaming quartz countertops, top-tier wifi-enabled stainless steel appliances, and chic brass accents set the stage. Immerse yourself in the open concept design, with ceramic tiles guiding you from the dining area to a cozy living space. Upstairs, three bedrooms and two bathrooms and laundry/utility closet provide an optimal layout for comfort and function. The owner’s suite with also Andersen door is a true retreat – a Romeo and Juliet balcony, expansive walk-in closet, and a spa-like en-suite bathroom replete with a luxurious bathtub and frameless glass door shower. Upgraded pantry, linen closet, master bedroom closet and the study room closet along with prewired for alarm (system and service can be transferred). Many updates made in this townhome including ceiling fans and hardware to give you that new home feel. Positioned in the heartbeat of the Hourglass District, this home is more than just a residence – it's a lifestyle. Enjoy the synergy of a community where innovation meets tradition, where contemporary design intertwines with a spirited vibe. Don't miss this golden chance to claim a piece of Orlando’s finest. Act now and embrace refined living! Schedule your viewing today! Follow link to 3D walk through tour: https://www.asteroommls.com/pviewer?hideleadgen=1&token=hNbbCO-jqEyAqxEVYC_fRg
